The central parity rate of the Chinese currency the Yuan, strengthened 43 pips to 6.3752 against the U.S. Dollar on Wednesday, according to the China Foreign Exchange Trade System. In China’s spot foreign exchange market, the Yuan is allowed to rise or fall by two per cent from the central parity rate each trading day.   Russia-Ukraine conflict: Trade recovery at risk, warns…     World Bank: poverty to rise over high food prices, currency…     Nasarawa attracts over $500m investment in three years   The central parity rate of the Yuan against the dollar is based on a weighted average of prices offered by market makers before opening of the interbank market each business day. (Xinhua/NAN)